---
import CaseStudy from "../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro";

const metrics = [
    { value: "MVP", label: "Stage" },
    { value: "LLMs + n8n", label: "Tech stack" },
];
---

<CaseStudy
    title="AI Patentability Assessment Platform"
    tag="AI Product · Intellectual Property"
    metrics={metrics}
>
    <section>
        <h2>Context</h2>
        <p>
            Patentia is an AI-powered platform that helps researchers and
            innovators evaluate if an invention can be patented — before
            spending money on a formal application. The platform uses AI to
            search prior art and generate patentability reports.
        </p>
        <p>
            I joined as Product Manager when the product was at MVP stage, with
            no customers yet and a roadmap that needed structure.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Challenge</h2>
        <p>
            Patentia was an early-stage product that needed structure. The team
            had a working MVP but the product flow, user understanding, and
            adoption strategy were still undefined.
        </p>
        <p>
            My role was to bring order to that — starting from research to
            understand who the users were, what was stopping them from adopting
            the product, and what the team should build next.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Discovery</h2>
        <p>
            I worked with insights from universities, research teams, innovation
            offices, and potential customers. From this research I identified
            user personas, the main adoption barriers, and product
            opportunities.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>My role</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Product Discovery</li>
            <li>Roadmap Planning</li>
            <li>User Persona Definition</li>
            <li>Wireframing</li>
            <li>Backlog Organization</li>
            <li>Jira Structuring</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            I helped the team translate research insights into product
            requirements and a development plan.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Technologies</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Large Language Models (LLMs)</li>
            <li>Prompt Engineering</li>
            <li>n8n</li>
            <li>ChatGPT</li>
            <li>AI-assisted prototyping</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Key learning</h2>
        <p>
            Building AI products is not only about the technology. Users need to
            trust the product before they use it. Identifying that barrier early
            — through research — was the most important contribution I made as
            PM.
        </p>
    </section>
</CaseStudy>
